8 - Run the pump for 30 min at maximum flow and record the following: (i) Suction and delivery pressures. (ii) Engine running temperature, which shall be within the engine manufacturer’s recommended limits. (iii) Engine oil pressure, which shall be within the engine manufacturer’s limits. (iv) Air temperature at pumpset. (v) Discharge pressure at three other flow rates between shut-off and maximum flow, one of which shall be at the duty flow rate. (vi) Check that the requirements of Clause 9.3.6.2 are complied with by holding the engine shutdown mechanism closed and simulating an automatic start signal until the engine has attempted to start for five automatic starting cycles. On the sixth starting cycle, return the engine shutdown mechanism to its normal starting position and check if the engine starts immediately. - AS2941.1-2013 – Section 12
